videos.description: Allonzo Trier knocks down a long 3-pointer early in the first half in his first game back for Arizona.
videos.headline: Trier sinks 3-pointer in return

videos.description: Kezie Okpala finds Oscar da Silva all alone underneath the basket for a wide-open dunk.
videos.headline: da Silva's dunk gives Stanford its first lead

videos.description: Deandre Ayton delivers a pass to a cutting Rawle Alkins for an and-1 layup.
videos.headline: Alkins hits a tough and-1 bucket

videos.description: Daejon Davis has to be helped off the court after an apparent leg injury.
videos.headline: Stanford's Davis leaves game after injury

videos.description: Deandre Ayton dribbles out of a double team and hits a layup while drawing a foul for a chance at a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Ayton escapes double team for 3-point play

videos.description: Arizona's Deandre Ayton delivers a bounce pass out of a double team to Keanu Pinder for a one-handed dunk.
videos.headline: Ayton drops a dime to Pinder for dunk

videos.description: Stanford's Daejon Davis, who missed some of the second half with a leg injury, anticipates a pass and races up the court for an easy dunk.
videos.headline: Davis' legs look fine after dunk

videos.description: Arizona loses Daejon Davis on offense as he turns the corner and gets to the rim for a wide-open dunk.
videos.headline: Davis makes Arizona pay for bad defense

videos.description: Arizona head coach Sean Miller addresses the media after a 75-67 win over Stanford to discuss recent allegations on the Wildcats' program.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCB Presser (Miller is 'focusing on the now') 2018/03/02

videos.headline: Miller is 'focusing on the now'
